WEBVTT

01:38.641 --> 01:41.978
[SLAM]

01:42.145 --> 01:43.980
HA HA!

01:44.147 --> 01:45.356
NO, SVEN.

01:45.523 --> 01:46.816
JUST PICKING IT UP,
MA'AM.

01:46.983 --> 01:48.985
THAT'S THE THIRD TIME
YOU'VE DROPPED IT.

01:49.152 --> 01:50.403
NOW I THINK YOU SHOULD
JUST LEAVE IT THERE.

01:50.570 --> 01:52.238
IT CAN'T FALL ANY FARTHER.

01:52.405 --> 01:53.490
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

01:53.656 --> 01:55.241
CHILDREN?

01:56.743 --> 01:59.954
YOU HAVE WORK TO DO.

02:00.121 --> 02:03.416
I'M GOING TO WRITE TOMORROW'S ARITHMETIC
ASSIGNMENT ON THE BOARD FOR ALL GRADES.

02:03.583 --> 02:07.170
YOU'LL HAVE TIME TO COPY IT
BEFORE YOU'RE DISMISSED.

02:32.111 --> 02:34.197
[THUMP]

02:43.665 --> 02:45.792
MISS BEADLE IS
A GOOD TEACHER.

02:45.959 --> 02:49.838
BUT MY NELLIE AND WILLIE TELL ME THAT
SHE'S NOT A VERY GOOD DISCIPLINARIAN.

02:50.004 --> 02:51.673
NOW, WHEN THE HARVEST
IS OVER,

02:51.840 --> 02:54.008
AND THE OLDER BOYS
COME TO SCHOOL,

02:54.175 --> 02:55.426
SHE'LL NEVER BE ABLE
TO COPE.

02:55.593 --> 03:00.348
SHE DID A GOOD JOB LAST
YEAR AND THE YEAR BEFORE.

03:00.515 --> 03:04.269
WELL, NOT WITH
THIS CROP OF BOYS.

03:04.435 --> 03:06.020
SHALL WE GO?

03:19.492 --> 03:21.035
HEY.

03:23.788 --> 03:25.874
[WHOOSH]

03:35.633 --> 03:37.594
GOOD GRIEF!

03:37.760 --> 03:39.888
[KIDS SHOUTING]

03:43.141 --> 03:45.184
STOP! NOW!

03:45.351 --> 03:46.853
NOW, YOU BE QUIET,
ALL OF YOU!

03:47.020 --> 03:48.646
NOW, GET BACK TO YOU PLACE!
GO ON!

03:48.813 --> 03:49.647
YES, SIR.

03:49.814 --> 03:50.648
GET BACK!

03:50.815 --> 03:51.649
YES, SIR.

03:51.816 --> 03:52.901
NOW, SIT!

03:55.486 --> 03:57.572
MISS BEADLE?

03:57.739 --> 03:58.740
ARE YOU HURT?

03:58.907 --> 04:00.575
NO, I'M FINE.

04:00.742 --> 04:03.286
I'M JUST FINE.

04:03.453 --> 04:06.331
AND I WAS RIGHT. YOU'LL
HAVE TO ADMIT THAT.

04:06.497 --> 04:09.626
I DON'T KNOW WHETHER
THIS IS A SCHOOLROOM

04:09.792 --> 04:11.377
OR BATTLEFIELD.

04:15.089 --> 04:17.091
I'M SORRY.

04:17.258 --> 04:18.968
IT WAS MY FAULT.

04:19.135 --> 04:19.928
WHAT?

04:20.094 --> 04:22.430
I THREW AN ERASER.

04:22.597 --> 04:25.558
I REALLY AM SORRY.

04:27.060 --> 04:28.853
YOU MAY TAKE YOUR SEAT,
LAURA.

04:29.020 --> 04:30.647
YES, MA'AM.

04:33.608 --> 04:37.820
MR. HANSON, MRS. OLESON, I CAN
ONLY ADD MY APOLOGY TO LAURA'S.

04:44.118 --> 04:46.496
CHILDREN, UH,
SCHOOL IS DISMISSED.

04:57.548 --> 05:00.426
A VERITABLE RIOT
IN OUR SCHOOLROOM.

05:00.593 --> 05:01.469
TSK TSK TSK.

05:01.636 --> 05:03.262
TWO BOYS WRESTLING
IS NOT A RIOT,

05:03.429 --> 05:05.807
BUT IT IS NOT GOOD
SCHOOLROOM BEHAVIOR, EITHER.

05:05.974 --> 05:07.934
WELL, I THINK THAT
THE WHOLE MATTER

05:08.101 --> 05:09.560
SHOULD GO BEFORE
THE SCHOOL BOARD,

05:09.727 --> 05:11.604
AND I BELIEVE
THAT OBVIOUSLY

05:11.771 --> 05:14.107
AN EMERGENCY MEETING
SHOULD BE CALLED.

05:14.273 --> 05:15.650
WE WILL COME TO THAT.

05:15.817 --> 05:17.944
UH, MISS BEADLE,
THE WHOLE SCHOOL BOARD

05:18.111 --> 05:19.904
HAS TO KNOW ABOUT
WHAT IS GOING ON,

05:20.071 --> 05:21.614
AND YOU ARE THE ONE
WHO CAN TELL THEM.

05:21.781 --> 05:25.118
UH, WOULD YOU COME
TO THE MEETING TONIGHT?

05:25.284 --> 05:26.536
OF COURSE.

05:26.703 --> 05:28.121
THANK YOU.

05:28.287 --> 05:30.164
UNTIL THEN, MISS BEADLE.

05:30.331 --> 05:32.125
COME ALONG, MR. HANSON.

05:34.002 --> 05:35.670
[DOOR CLOSES]

05:40.133 --> 05:43.428
THERE'S NOTHING PERSONAL ABOUT
ANY OF THIS, MISS BEADLE.

05:43.594 --> 05:50.727
WE'RE JUST TRYING TO DO THE BEST
WE CAN FOR PUPILS AND THE TEACHER.

05:50.893 --> 05:52.979
UH, THIS, UM...

05:53.146 --> 05:57.525
EXPLOSION THAT, UH, HAPPENED
IN THE CLASSROOM TODAY...

05:57.692 --> 05:59.694
CAN YOU TELL US
WHAT CAUSED IT?

05:59.861 --> 06:01.320
I DIDN'T SEE IT START.

06:01.487 --> 06:05.992
I GUESS IT WAS... SOMETHING
TRIGGERED A SUDDEN FLARE OF ANGER.

06:06.159 --> 06:09.078
DO YOU THINK
IT'LL HAPPEN AGAIN?

06:09.245 --> 06:10.371
I DON'T KNOW.

06:10.538 --> 06:13.499
THEN IT HAS
HAPPENED BEFORE.

06:13.666 --> 06:15.543
WHY, YES,
A FEW TIMES.

06:15.710 --> 06:17.962
SOME OF THE OLDER BOYS
ARE VERY DIFFICULT TO HANDLE.

06:18.129 --> 06:20.381
OH, MY, THAT'S
AN UNDERSTATEMENT.

06:20.548 --> 06:22.717
I'VE TRIED TALKING TO
THEIR PARENTS ABOUT IT.

06:22.884 --> 06:25.136
THEY SHOW
NO INTEREST.

06:25.303 --> 06:26.429
WHEN THE OLDER BOYS
ACT UP,

06:26.596 --> 06:27.805
THE YOUNGER ONES
FOLLOW SUIT,

06:27.972 --> 06:29.140
AND THEN THEY GET THE
ATTENTION THAT THEY WANT.

06:29.307 --> 06:31.517
Harriet: MISS BEADLE,
YOU ARE BEING PAID

06:31.684 --> 06:34.437
TO HAVE STRICT DISCIPLINE
IN THIS SCHOOLROOM.

06:34.604 --> 06:37.065
MRS. OLESON,
I'M BEING PAID TO TEACH.

06:37.231 --> 06:39.025
OH? WELL, THEN YOU CAN'T
VERY WELL DO THAT,

06:39.192 --> 06:42.361
CAN YOU, IF THERE'S
A RIOT GOING ON IN HERE.

06:42.528 --> 06:44.238
AND HOW WOULD YOU GO ABOUT
DISCIPLINING A BOY

06:44.405 --> 06:45.698
WHO OUTWEIGHS YOU
BY 50 POUNDS

06:45.865 --> 06:48.701
AND IS A HEAD TALLER
THAN YOU ARE?

06:48.868 --> 06:51.329
THAT IS NOT
MY PROBLEM.

06:51.496 --> 06:53.873
IT IS YOURS, AND
DON'T YOU FORGET

06:54.040 --> 06:55.792
THAT THE BIGGER BOYS WILL
SOON BE COMING IN HERE

06:55.958 --> 06:57.210
WHEN THE HARVEST
IS OVER.

06:57.376 --> 06:59.670
MRS. OLESON, PLEASE.

06:59.837 --> 07:01.798
MISS BEADLE,

07:01.964 --> 07:04.842
WHEN THE BIGGER BOYS
COME IN FROM THE FIELDS,

07:05.009 --> 07:07.887
WILL YOU BE ABLE
TO CONTROL THEM?

07:08.054 --> 07:09.764
WELL, I'LL
TRY MY BEST.

07:09.931 --> 07:14.185
OH, BUT YOU DO
HAVE SOME DOUBTS.

07:19.065 --> 07:20.900
YES. YES. I DO.

07:25.446 --> 07:28.574
WELL, WE THANK YOU FOR
YOUR HONESTY, MISS BEADLE,

07:28.741 --> 07:31.035
AND FOR COMING IN
TONIGHT.

07:42.004 --> 07:46.092
I'M GOING TO BE GRADING PAPERS
UNTIL QUITE LATE.

07:46.259 --> 07:48.845
I WOULD APPRECIATE YOUR DECISION
THIS EVENING.

07:54.142 --> 07:55.434
[DOOR OPENS]

07:55.601 --> 07:56.811
[SIGHS]

07:56.978 --> 07:57.937
[DOOR CLOSES]

07:58.104 --> 07:59.397
HMM.

08:08.281 --> 08:10.158
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

08:26.799 --> 08:29.635
MR. INGALLS. COME IN.

08:29.802 --> 08:31.304
THANK YOU.

08:34.307 --> 08:35.600
WOULD YOU LIKE SOME TEA?

08:35.766 --> 08:37.476
NO. NO, THANK YOU.

08:38.895 --> 08:41.898
I TAKE IT THEY'VE
MADE THEIR DECISION.

08:43.191 --> 08:45.902
YEAH. THEY...

08:46.068 --> 08:47.278
THEY DECIDED
THAT A MALE TEACHER

08:47.445 --> 08:49.655
WOULD BE BETTER ABLE
TO COPE WITH THE OLDER BOYS.

08:52.575 --> 08:54.202
I SEE.

09:04.754 --> 09:06.380
I KNOW IT'S VERY
LITTLE CONSOLATION,

09:06.547 --> 09:08.507
BUT THE VOTE
WASN'T UNANIMOUS.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.428
I'M SORRY.

09:14.096 --> 09:15.598
I KNOW.

09:18.184 --> 09:21.020
YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY,
I'M RELIEVED.

09:21.187 --> 09:23.648
I WAS DREADING
HARVEST TIME.

09:23.814 --> 09:27.568
ALL THOSE BOYS COMING
BACK TO SCHOOL...MEN.

09:30.947 --> 09:33.532
PERHAPS IF I HAD BEEN
A BETTER TEACHER...

09:33.699 --> 09:35.993
YOU'RE A FINE TEACHER.

09:36.911 --> 09:39.288
YOU CAN'T
BLAME YOURSELF.

09:39.455 --> 09:43.376
WELL, THAT'S THE TROUBLE
WITH BEING A TEACHER.

09:43.542 --> 09:46.629
THERE'S NO ONE ELSE
IN THE SCHOOLROOM TO BLAME.

09:54.095 --> 09:57.765
MY CHILDREN PAINTED ME
THIS CARD LAST CHRISTMAS.

09:57.932 --> 10:00.226
ISN'T IT BEAUTIFUL?

10:00.393 --> 10:03.229
"WE LOVE YOU,
MISS BEADLE."

10:03.396 --> 10:05.356
AND THEY ALL SIGNED IT.

10:07.984 --> 10:10.653
"WE LOVE YOU,
MISS BEADLE."

10:12.571 --> 10:14.073
BOARD WANTED TO KNOW
IF YOU WOULD STAY ON

10:14.240 --> 10:16.033
UNTIL THE NEW TEACHER
ARRIVES.

10:18.744 --> 10:20.246
OF COURSE.

10:24.792 --> 10:27.586
MR. INGALLS,
I'D APPRECIATE IT

10:27.753 --> 10:29.547
IF YOU WOULDN'T MENTION IT
TO THE CHILDREN

10:29.714 --> 10:33.467
UNTIL AFTER
THE NEW TEACHER ARRIVES.

10:33.634 --> 10:36.053
I UNDERSTAND.

10:43.769 --> 10:45.813
WELL,
I'D BETTER BE GOING.

10:45.980 --> 10:47.940
MR. INGALLS.

10:48.107 --> 10:49.900
YEAH?

10:50.067 --> 10:52.611
LAURA...

10:54.447 --> 10:57.783
LAURA'S DOING MUCH BETTER
IN HER FRACTIONS,

10:57.950 --> 11:01.454
BUT I THINK SHE NEEDS TO WORK
A LITTLE HARDER ON THEM.

11:03.247 --> 11:05.541
I'LL SEE THAT SHE DOES.

11:25.227 --> 11:27.855
MY PA TOLD MY MA,
AND I HEARD THEM.

11:28.022 --> 11:29.398
WE'RE GETTING A MAN TEACHER.

11:29.565 --> 11:30.566
Sven: WHAT'S WRONG
WITH MISS BEADLE?

11:30.733 --> 11:31.984
IS SHE SICK
OR SOMETHING?

11:32.151 --> 11:33.486
NO, SHE'S NOT SICK.

11:33.652 --> 11:35.029
Mary: THEN WHY ARE WE
GETTING A NEW TEACHER?

11:35.196 --> 11:36.989
WHY DO YOU THINK?
IT'S LAURA INGALLS' FAULT.

11:37.156 --> 11:38.491
THAT'S NOT TRUE,
NELLIE OLESON.

11:38.657 --> 11:40.326
IF IT'S ANYBODY'S FAULT,
IT'S WILLIE'S.

11:40.493 --> 11:41.535
HE STARTED IT.

11:41.702 --> 11:42.995
DID NOT! DID NOT!

11:43.162 --> 11:44.622
YOU DID TOO!

11:44.789 --> 11:47.416
Nellie:
IT'S LAURA'S FAULT.

11:47.583 --> 11:49.794
YOU SAY THAT AGAIN,
AND I'LL SLAP YOUR FACE!

11:49.960 --> 11:52.171
YOU TRY IT, I'LL PULL YOUR
HAIR OUT BY THE ROOTS.

11:52.338 --> 11:54.048
GIRLS, THAT'S ENOUGH!

11:58.052 --> 11:59.804
NOW, YOU HAVE 5 MINUTES
OF RECESS LEFT.

11:59.970 --> 12:02.181
I SUGGEST YOU USE IT FOR
PLAYING AND NOT FIGHTING.

12:02.348 --> 12:04.683
YES, MA'AM.
LET'S GO.

12:08.646 --> 12:09.980
IS NELLIE RIGHT?

12:10.147 --> 12:12.858
ARE WE GOING TO HAVE
A NEW TEACHER?

12:14.693 --> 12:17.947
YES, LAURA.
TOMORROW'S MY LAST DAY.

12:19.198 --> 12:21.492
PA MUST HAVE KNOWN.

12:23.077 --> 12:25.955
I ASKED HIM NOT TO SAY ANYTHING
FOR MY SAKE.

12:29.917 --> 12:31.502
IT WAS MY FAULT.

12:31.669 --> 12:33.337
I THREW THAT ERASER.

12:33.504 --> 12:37.049
NO, DARLING.
IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.

12:37.216 --> 12:43.222
WHOEVER HE IS, HE WON'T BE AS GOOD
AS TEACHER AS YOU, MISS BEADLE.

12:44.390 --> 12:46.684
WELL, THANK YOU
VERY MUCH.

12:53.899 --> 12:56.402
WONDER WHAT THE NEW
TEACHER WILL BE LIKE.

12:56.569 --> 12:58.863
REAL MEAN,
PROBABLY.

12:59.029 --> 13:00.406
WHY DO YOU SAY THAT?

13:00.573 --> 13:02.241
BECAUSE THAT'S WHY
THEY WANT A NEW TEACHER,

13:02.408 --> 13:04.869
SOMEONE BIG AND MEAN
TO SCARE THE OLDER BOYS.

13:05.035 --> 13:07.621
HE'D HAVE TO BE AWFUL
BIG TO SCARE HERMAN.

13:07.788 --> 13:09.165
WHO'S HERMAN?

13:09.331 --> 13:10.708
HERMAN STONE,

13:10.875 --> 13:12.710
JUST MOVED INTO
THE OLD HARRISON FARM.

13:12.877 --> 13:14.253
I SAW HIM
THE OTHER DAY.

13:14.420 --> 13:16.755
HE'S TALL ENOUGH TO LOOK
DOWN AT THE TOP OF A SILO.

13:16.922 --> 13:19.592
WELL, HE BETTER NOT PICK
ON ME, OR I'LL KICK HIM.

13:19.758 --> 13:21.302
YOU JUST STAY
OUT OF TROUBLE.

13:21.469 --> 13:22.845
YOU HEARD WHAT MA
SAID TONIGHT--

13:23.012 --> 13:25.973
DO YOUR BEST AND TRY TO HELP
THE NEW TEACHER ALL YOU CAN.

13:26.140 --> 13:28.642
I WILL.
GOOD NIGHT.

13:28.809 --> 13:30.936
GOOD NIGHT.

13:38.110 --> 13:40.905
YOU KNOW SOMETHING?

13:41.071 --> 13:42.948
WHAT?

13:43.115 --> 13:46.452
I'LL BET THAT NELLIE OLESON
BRINGS THE NEW TEACHER AN APPLE.

13:46.619 --> 13:49.830
HEE HEE! YOU'RE
PROBABLY RIGHT.

13:49.997 --> 13:52.291
MAYBE HE'LL
HATE APPLES.

13:52.458 --> 13:54.627
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

13:54.793 --> 13:57.129
YEAH. HO HO HO!

13:57.296 --> 13:59.215
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT.

13:59.381 --> 14:02.343
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

14:02.510 --> 14:05.346
HA HA HA!
HA HA HA!

14:31.497 --> 14:32.623
SHOULD BE ANY MINUTE.

14:32.790 --> 14:35.501
I SURE HOPE IT COMES
BEFORE THE BELL RINGS.

14:47.888 --> 14:49.348
HERE IT COMES.

14:49.515 --> 14:51.392
HERE IT COMES.

15:01.193 --> 15:03.028
BYE!

15:03.195 --> 15:07.199
BYE, MISS BEADLE!
HURRY BACK!

15:07.366 --> 15:08.742
BYE!

15:08.909 --> 15:11.328
[BELL RINGING]

15:40.441 --> 15:41.567
GOOD MORNING.

15:52.286 --> 15:54.580
[CHILDREN TALKING]

16:00.836 --> 16:02.504
SILENCE!

16:27.863 --> 16:30.449
GOOD.

16:30.616 --> 16:34.787
MY NAME IS MR. APPLEWOOD.
IT'S WRITTEN ON THE BOARD.

16:34.953 --> 16:36.121
AS YOU ALL KNOW BY NOW,

16:36.288 --> 16:38.540
MISS BEADLE IS NO LONGER
YOUR TEACHER.

16:38.707 --> 16:40.250
I AM.

16:40.417 --> 16:41.960
FROM THIS MOMENT FORWARD,

16:42.127 --> 16:45.464
THIS CLASSROOM
WILL BE RUN BY ME.

16:47.132 --> 16:49.510
IS THAT CLEAR?

16:51.720 --> 16:53.722
GOOD.

16:53.889 --> 16:55.891
SO THAT THERE IS NO MISTAKE
IN THE FUTURE,

16:56.058 --> 17:01.230
THERE WILL BE CERTAIN NEW RULES
WHICH YOU WILL ALL ABIDE BY...

17:01.397 --> 17:04.525
WITHOUT DEVIATION.

17:04.692 --> 17:07.528
THOSE RULES ARE AS FOLLOWS.

17:07.695 --> 17:10.489
YOU WILL SPEAK
ONLY WHEN SPOKEN TO.

17:10.656 --> 17:12.950
NO ONE IS TO LEAVE HIS SEAT
WITHOUT PERMISSION.

17:13.117 --> 17:16.120
THERE WILL BE NO WHISPERING,
NO WRITING OF NOTES.

17:16.286 --> 17:25.462
ANY ASSIGNMENT OR TEST PAPER HANDED IN WITH AN
ERASURE ON IT WILL RECEIVE A FAILING GRADE.

17:25.629 --> 17:30.092
EVERY ASSIGNMENT WILL HAVE
THE STUDENT'S NAME AND GRADE

17:30.259 --> 17:33.011
CLEARLY WRITTEN IN THE UPPER
RIGHT-HAND CORNER.

17:33.178 --> 17:34.304
IF THAT IS NOT EXACT,

17:34.471 --> 17:37.850
THAT STUDENT WILL RECEIVE
A FAILING GRADE.

17:39.309 --> 17:41.353
IT'S VERY SIMPLE.

17:41.520 --> 17:46.358
ANY STUDENT CAUGHT CHEATING
WILL RECEIVE A FAILING GRADE...

17:46.525 --> 17:51.029
AND WILL HAVE NO RECESS
OR LUNCH HOUR FOR ONE WEEK.

17:58.996 --> 18:01.248
IS EVERYONE CLEAR SO FAR?

18:05.085 --> 18:06.628
GOOD.

18:06.795 --> 18:07.921
GOOD.

18:08.088 --> 18:09.673
GOOD.

18:09.840 --> 18:13.969
I HAVE ALSO HEARD THAT
THERE HAS BEEN A, UM...

18:14.136 --> 18:16.847
DISCIPLINARY PROBLEM
IN THIS CLASSROOM.

18:17.014 --> 18:18.766
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

18:18.932 --> 18:20.350
LET ME ASSURE YOU...

18:20.517 --> 18:25.272
THAT...IS NO LONGER TRUE.

18:27.483 --> 18:30.527
NOW, I THINK
I'VE MADE MYSELF CLEAR.

18:30.694 --> 18:34.072
LET'S SEE HOW WELL
YOU UNDERSTAND.

18:34.239 --> 18:36.450
AS YOUR FIRST LESSON FOR TODAY,

18:36.617 --> 18:42.498
YOU WILL WRITE DOWN THE RULES
I HAVE JUST GIVEN YOU.

18:45.334 --> 18:47.211
NOW!

19:27.084 --> 19:30.087
LAURA INGALLS?

19:30.254 --> 19:31.964
YES, SIR?

19:32.130 --> 19:35.467
WHAT DO YOU HAVE
UNDER YOUR HAND?

19:37.803 --> 19:39.638
JUST A PIECE OF PAPER.

19:39.805 --> 19:42.307
PIECE OF PAPER, HUH?

19:43.642 --> 19:45.978
BRING IT TO ME.

19:46.144 --> 19:48.021
NOW.

19:56.613 --> 19:59.116
DID I TELL YOU
TO STOP STUDYING?!

20:33.233 --> 20:35.485
HOLD OUT YOUR HAND.

20:42.284 --> 20:44.328
[SMACK]

20:44.494 --> 20:46.163
[SMACK]

20:48.540 --> 20:51.084
FOR BEING TARDY...

20:51.251 --> 20:52.920
FOR WRITING
AND PASSING NOTES.

20:53.086 --> 20:54.880
BUT I DIDN'T.

20:55.047 --> 21:00.427
OH, IT JUST GOT THERE ON YOUR
DESK BY MAGIC, IS THAT IT?

21:00.594 --> 21:04.431
WELL, NO, SIR.

21:04.598 --> 21:07.059
THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

21:07.225 --> 21:10.896
SINCE YOU LIKE TO WRITE,

21:11.063 --> 21:13.398
YOU'RE GOING TO DO
A LOT OF IT.

21:37.214 --> 21:39.508
SCHOOL IS DISMISSED,

21:39.675 --> 21:43.762
EXCEPT FOR THOSE WHO STILL HAVE
WORK ON THE BLACKBOARD.

22:03.949 --> 22:05.117
AND I WAS SO BUSY WRITING,

22:05.283 --> 22:07.035
THAT I DIDN'T HAVE TIME
TO STUDY MY SPELLING,

22:07.202 --> 22:10.330
AND IT JUST MEANT I HAD TO STAY
AFTER SCHOOL AND WRITE.

22:10.497 --> 22:13.000
JUST WASN'T FAIR.

22:13.166 --> 22:16.044
THIS LONG DMSION
SURE IS HARD.

22:16.211 --> 22:17.754
YEAH, NOW WAIT A MINUTE,
HALF-PINT.

22:17.921 --> 22:19.715
YOU HAVEN'T FINISHED TELLING ME
ABOUT THE PROBLEM AT SCHOOL.

22:19.881 --> 22:22.467
NOW, DID YOU TO EXPLAIN TO MR.
APPLEWOOD THAT IT WASN'T YOUR NOTE?

22:22.634 --> 22:24.136
I TRIED TO.

22:24.302 --> 22:26.138
HE WOULDN'T
LISTEN, PA.

22:26.304 --> 22:27.264
NOW, IN MY EXPERIENCE,

22:27.431 --> 22:29.474
TEACHERS ALWAYS TRY
TO BE VERY FAIR.

22:29.641 --> 22:31.226
YOUR MOTHER'S RIGHT,
HALF-PINT.

22:31.393 --> 22:33.020
WHEN MR. APPLEWOOD FINDS OUT
WHAT A GOOD STUDENT YOU ARE,

22:33.186 --> 22:34.896
THINGS WILL BE
A LOT BETTER.

22:35.063 --> 22:36.314
I SURE HOPE IT'S SOON.

22:36.481 --> 22:40.694
ALL THAT WRITING'S
GETTING ME BEHIND.

22:40.861 --> 22:44.823
29 INTO 114...

22:46.450 --> 22:49.411
SUPERB.

22:49.578 --> 22:51.580
I AM TRULY GRATEFUL
THAT YOU ALLOW ME

22:51.747 --> 22:53.123
TO SHARE MY SUPPERS
WITH YOU.

22:53.290 --> 22:54.624
IT'S THE LEAST WE CAN DO.

22:54.791 --> 22:56.918
WELL, IT'S OUR PLEASURE.

22:57.085 --> 23:01.840
I ALWAYS FEEL THAT THE ONLY THING HARDER
TO FIND IN WALNUT GROVE THAN GOOD FOOD

23:02.007 --> 23:03.425
IS INTELLIGENT TALK.

23:03.592 --> 23:06.303
HMM.

23:10.432 --> 23:13.685
ORDINARILY,
MR. APPLEWOOD,

23:13.852 --> 23:15.604
I DON'T LIKE
TO CARRY TALES--

23:15.771 --> 23:18.190
THEN DON'T.

23:18.356 --> 23:19.232
Willie:
MAY I BE EXCUSED?

23:19.399 --> 23:21.276
NO, WILLIE.

23:21.443 --> 23:25.363
NELS, I FEEL THAT WE OWE IT
TO MR. APPLEWOOD.

23:25.530 --> 23:27.699
AND I APPRECIATE
YOUR HELP.

23:27.866 --> 23:32.370
LAURA INGALLS IS
A LITTLE TROUBLEMAKER.

23:32.537 --> 23:34.998
HARRIET, I THINK
YOU'RE EXAGGERATING.

23:35.165 --> 23:39.086
I AM ONLY STATING
A SIMPLE TRUTH.

23:39.252 --> 23:40.712
WELL, I HAVE ALWAYS
FOUND HER TO BE

23:40.879 --> 23:42.506
VERY PLEASANT
AND WELL-BEHAVED.

23:42.672 --> 23:46.843
WELL, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN AROUND
WHEN SHE'S BEEN UP TO HER TRICKS!

23:47.010 --> 23:48.929
ISN'T THAT SO, CHILDREN?

23:49.096 --> 23:51.473
YES'M. MAY I BE EXCUSED?

23:51.640 --> 23:52.641
NO!

23:52.808 --> 23:54.184
SHE DOES WHISPER
A LOT.

23:54.351 --> 23:56.478
SHE WAS KIND OF
MISS BEADLE'S PET.

23:56.645 --> 23:59.815
AHH. WELL,
I THANK YOU ALL.

23:59.981 --> 24:02.692
FOREWARNED
IS FOREARMED.

24:13.245 --> 24:16.540
Sven: GEE, UH, I'M SURE SORRY ABOUT
PASSING THAT NOTE YESTERDAY.

24:16.706 --> 24:18.083
YOU'RE SORRY?

24:18.250 --> 24:19.668
I GOT PUNISHED.

24:19.835 --> 24:21.503
WELL, I TALKED TO
THE OTHER GUYS, AND, UH,

24:21.670 --> 24:24.381
WE'RE GOING TO HELP YOU GET EVEN
WITH THAT OLD CRAB APPLEWOOD.

24:24.548 --> 24:25.757
PLEASE DON'T.

24:25.924 --> 24:27.509
BUT WE WANT TO.

24:27.676 --> 24:30.929
IF YOU'RE MY FRIEND,
YOU WON'T DO ANYTHING.

24:31.096 --> 24:33.598
I AM YOUR FRIEND. THAT'S
WHY I WANT TO HELP.

24:33.765 --> 24:37.227
NO. I'M IN TROUBLE
ENOUGH.

24:42.482 --> 24:44.484
TIME'S UP.

24:44.651 --> 24:47.779
WILLIE OLESON,
WILL YOU COLLECT THE PAPERS?

25:07.549 --> 25:10.010
HERMAN!

25:10.177 --> 25:11.845
COME UP HERE!

25:20.645 --> 25:24.274
YOU ARE AN HOUR LATE. YOU MISSED
YOUR HISTORY EXAMINATION.

25:24.441 --> 25:26.318
YEAH.

25:26.484 --> 25:29.154
KINGS AND BATTLES
DON'T MEAN NOTHING.

25:29.321 --> 25:31.615
NOT IF YOU KNOW HOW
TO PLANT AND PLOW,

25:31.781 --> 25:34.117
HOW MUCH THEY'RE PAYING
FOR CORN.

25:34.284 --> 25:36.828
AHH...
A KNOW-IT-ALL, HUH?

25:36.995 --> 25:38.997
WELL, I THINK
I CAN TEACH YOU

25:39.164 --> 25:43.168
TO BE ON TIME
FOR SCHOOL.

25:43.335 --> 25:45.086
PUT OUT YOUR HAND.

25:49.299 --> 25:50.634
[LAUGHTER]

25:50.800 --> 25:53.053
GET BACK TO WORK,
ALL OF YOU!

25:56.348 --> 25:58.725
HOLD OUT YOUR HAND.

26:03.438 --> 26:04.689
[SMACK]

26:08.026 --> 26:10.946
[SMACK]

26:11.112 --> 26:12.906
TEACH YOU
TO COME LATE.

26:13.073 --> 26:15.367
TAUGHT ME YOU CAN'T
HIT HARD ENOUGH TO TICKLE.

26:15.533 --> 26:17.702
[SNICKERING]

26:19.371 --> 26:21.539
GO BACK TO YOUR SEAT.

26:21.706 --> 26:22.999
SURE.

26:23.166 --> 26:24.376
REASON I WAS LATE,

26:24.542 --> 26:27.337
ONE OF OUR COWS
WAS BIRTHING.

26:32.717 --> 26:35.470
LAURA INGALLS,

26:35.637 --> 26:39.015
SINCE YOU DON'T SEEM TO HAVE
ENOUGH WORK TO OCCUPY YOUR MIND,

26:39.182 --> 26:42.352
I WILL GIVE YOU
SOME MORE WORK.

27:14.759 --> 27:16.594
[CHILDREN SHOUTING]

27:20.724 --> 27:22.600
WHOA!

27:22.767 --> 27:23.810
HEY, YOU ALL RIGHT?

27:23.977 --> 27:25.937
YEAH. YEAH,
I'M ALL RIGHT.

27:26.104 --> 27:27.564
HAVE SOME.

27:27.731 --> 27:29.149
THANKS, HERMAN.

27:37.991 --> 27:40.201
Mary: HI, SVEN.

27:43.079 --> 27:44.706
BEEN LOOKING FOR YOU.

27:44.873 --> 27:47.500
I'VE BEEN RIGHT HERE.

27:47.667 --> 27:49.794
THAT CRAB APPLE.

27:49.961 --> 27:51.880
HERMAN JUST LAUGHED
AT HIM.

27:54.132 --> 27:56.384
THAT'S WHY HE'S BEEN
PICKING ON YOU.

27:56.551 --> 27:58.094
HE'S GOING
TO BE SORRY, TOO.

27:58.261 --> 28:00.013
PLEASE, SVEN.
NO TRICKS.

28:00.180 --> 28:01.514
AFTER WHAT HE DONE
TO YOU?

28:01.681 --> 28:03.558
HE'S BEEN NICE
TO ME TODAY.

28:03.725 --> 28:07.312
NICE? HE GAVE YOU A FLUNK ON
YOUR HOMEWORK, DIDN'T HE?

28:07.479 --> 28:09.356
FOR HIM, THAT'S NICE.

28:09.522 --> 28:11.399
I GOTTA GO.

28:19.449 --> 28:22.118
I'M GOING TO STUDY
MY SPELLING.

28:30.001 --> 28:32.003
[DOOR OPENS,
CHILDREN CLAMORING]

28:36.007 --> 28:38.426
HEY, MAN, WE'LL GO
OVER THERE TOMORROW...

28:38.593 --> 28:40.220
OR AFTER SCHOOL
TODAY.

28:40.387 --> 28:41.888
SURE, WHY NOT?

28:44.974 --> 28:47.727
ALL STUDENTS,
PAPER AND PENCILS.

29:00.698 --> 29:02.992
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

29:06.996 --> 29:09.958
DESTRUCTION OF PROPERTY,
AND YOU THINK IT'S FUNNY?

29:10.125 --> 29:11.876
WELL, I DON'T!

29:14.546 --> 29:16.047
LAURA INGALLS, COME HERE.

29:23.680 --> 29:26.433
YOU'RE EXPELLED.
GO HOME.

29:28.184 --> 29:29.894
MR. APPLEWOOD,
PLEASE--

29:30.061 --> 29:31.563
NOW!

30:21.571 --> 30:25.325
HALF-PINT,
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

30:25.492 --> 30:27.494
HEY.

30:27.660 --> 30:28.995
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

30:29.162 --> 30:30.622
NOW, COME ON.
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

30:30.788 --> 30:33.917
HE EXPELLED ME, PA.
HE SENT ME HOME.

30:34.083 --> 30:36.836
WELL, WHY DID HE
EXPEL YOU?

30:38.796 --> 30:40.798
HE SAID THAT I PUT...

30:40.965 --> 30:43.218
INK ALL OVER
HIS PAPERS.

30:43.384 --> 30:45.428
BUT I DIDN'T, PA.
HONEST, I DIDN'T.

30:45.595 --> 30:47.263
ALL RIGHT, NOW.

30:47.430 --> 30:49.182
NOW, IT'S GOING TO BE
ALL RIGHT.

30:49.349 --> 30:50.808
I BELIEVE YOU.

30:52.852 --> 30:54.312
NOW, DON'T YOU WORRY.
IT'S GOING TO BE ALL RIGHT.

30:54.479 --> 30:56.105
YOU JUST GO WASH UP.

30:58.942 --> 31:00.360
I LOVE YOU.

31:00.527 --> 31:02.487
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

31:12.664 --> 31:13.957
Caroline: SHE GOT OFF
ON THE WRONG FOOT

31:14.123 --> 31:17.210
FROM THE MOMENT MR. APPLEWOOD
CAME INTO THE SCHOOL.

31:17.377 --> 31:20.338
I KNOW. I'LL TALK TO
HIM IN THE MORNING.

31:20.505 --> 31:22.465
OF COURSE, SHE'S NOT
THE STUDENT MARY IS,

31:22.632 --> 31:25.176
BUT SHE DOES TRY HARD.

31:25.343 --> 31:26.928
I KNOW SHE DOES.

31:27.095 --> 31:30.181
MARY DOES SAY
THAT HE'S UNFAIR.

31:30.348 --> 31:31.683
WELL,
MARY WOULD SAY THAT

31:31.849 --> 31:34.561
ABOUT ANYBODY
THAT HURT LAURA.

31:34.727 --> 31:39.857
YES, BUT I KNOW SHE DIDN'T
POUR INK IN HIS SATCHEL.

31:40.024 --> 31:40.942
I KNOW THAT,

31:41.109 --> 31:42.151
AND THAT'S
ONE OF THE THINGS

31:42.318 --> 31:43.403
THAT I'M GOING
TO TELL HIM

31:43.570 --> 31:45.738
IN THE MORNING.

31:45.905 --> 31:50.368
CHARLES, YOU HAVE BEEN
KNOWN TO LOSE YOUR TEMPER.

31:50.535 --> 31:54.539
NOW, IF YOU DO, YOU COULD MAKE
THINGS EVEN WORSE FOR LAURA.

31:54.706 --> 31:57.458
I'LL BE VERY NICE
TO HIM...

31:59.210 --> 32:02.380
IN THE MORNING.

32:02.547 --> 32:03.381
GOOD NIGHT.

32:03.548 --> 32:05.216
GOOD NIGHT.

32:07.218 --> 32:08.720
EVERYBODY'S
BEEN FINE HERE?

32:08.886 --> 32:10.430
HOW'S YOUR READING
GOING?

32:10.597 --> 32:12.557
Girl: FINE.

32:12.724 --> 32:14.559
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME?

32:14.726 --> 32:16.936
AND WILL YOU
COME VISIT ME?

32:19.564 --> 32:20.815
MISS BEADLE.

32:20.982 --> 32:22.066
OH, MR. INGALLS,
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

32:22.233 --> 32:23.067
WHEN DID YOU GET BACK?

32:23.234 --> 32:24.068
YESTERDAY.

32:24.235 --> 32:25.194
HOW WAS YOUR TRIP?

32:25.361 --> 32:26.863
IT WAS FUN, BUT AM I
GLAD TO BE BACK.

32:27.030 --> 32:28.740
WE MISSED YOU SO MUCH.

32:28.906 --> 32:30.283
WELL, THAT'S
NICE TO KNOW.

32:30.450 --> 32:32.201
HOW'S SCHOOL?

32:34.037 --> 32:36.080
ALL RIGHT.

32:36.247 --> 32:39.000
JUST ALL RIGHT?

32:39.167 --> 32:41.961
LAURA, I KNOW YOU HAVE TROUBLE
WITH FRACTIONS.

32:42.128 --> 32:44.255
NOW, IF YOU NEED SOME HELP,
YOU COME SEE ME, OK?

32:44.422 --> 32:46.090
OK.
YOU, TOO, MARY.

32:46.257 --> 32:47.091
WE WILL,
MISS BEADLE.

32:47.258 --> 32:48.926
THANKS.
THANKS.

32:49.093 --> 32:51.095
WE'RE GLAD YOU'RE HOME. MAYBE YOU
CAN HAVE SUPPER WITH US THIS WEEK.

32:51.262 --> 32:52.430
OH, I'D LOVE THAT.

32:52.597 --> 32:53.473
I'LL TELL CAROLINE.

32:53.640 --> 32:54.766
GOOD. GIVE HER
MY BEST, WILL YOU?

32:54.932 --> 32:55.933
I CERTAINLY WILL.
BYE-BYE.

32:56.100 --> 32:57.185
GOOD- BYE,
MISS BEADLE.

32:57.352 --> 32:58.436
BYE, MISS BEADLE.

32:58.603 --> 33:00.188
BYE.

33:04.108 --> 33:06.944
RUINED. TOTALLY RUINED.

33:07.111 --> 33:10.615
YOUR DAUGHTER DIDN'T LIKE
THE MARK I GAVE HER.

33:10.782 --> 33:12.450
SHE WAS ALONE
IN THIS ROOM.

33:12.617 --> 33:16.162
ONE PLUS ONE,
MR. INGALLS.

33:16.329 --> 33:18.414
OF COURSE, THERE ARE
TWO DOORS TO THE SCHOOL.

33:18.581 --> 33:21.626
WERE YOU IN A POSITION TO WATCH
BOTH OF THEM ALL THE TIME?

33:21.793 --> 33:23.002
WHAT ARE
YOU GETTING AT?

33:23.169 --> 33:24.295
JUST THAT IT WAS
MY UNDERSTANDING

33:24.462 --> 33:25.797
THAT YOU WERE OUT IN
FRONT OF THE BUILDING.

33:25.963 --> 33:28.591
YES. YES, I WAS.

33:28.758 --> 33:29.884
WELL, THEN IT
IS POSSIBLE

33:30.051 --> 33:31.594
SOMEONE COULD HAVE
COME IN THE BACK DOOR...

33:31.761 --> 33:33.971
BEFORE LAURA CAME
IN THE SCHOOL.

33:36.099 --> 33:37.809
THIS IS A BARE
POSSIBILITY. YES.

33:37.975 --> 33:39.477
THERE IS A POSSIBILITY.

33:39.644 --> 33:41.896
I MEAN, THEY COULD HAVE COME IN,
SPILLED THE INK, AND THEN LEFT.

33:42.063 --> 33:44.899
MY DAUGHTER SAID SHE DIDN'T
DO IT, AND I BELIEVE HER.

33:46.150 --> 33:50.488
YES, WELL, IN THE
ABSENCE OF CLEAR PROOF

33:50.655 --> 33:51.948
ONE WAY OR THE OTHER,

33:52.115 --> 33:55.034
LAURA, YOU MAY
RETURN TO SCHOOL.

33:55.201 --> 33:56.828
THANK YOU, SIR.

33:56.994 --> 33:59.831
AND YOU MAY RING
THE BELL.

33:59.997 --> 34:00.998
IT'S TIME.

34:01.165 --> 34:02.834
YES, SIR.

34:05.670 --> 34:07.130
I'M NOT SAYING SHE DOESN'T
DO A FEW THINGS WRONG,

34:07.296 --> 34:08.840
BUT SHE USUALLY
TELLS THE TRUTH.

34:09.006 --> 34:11.175
THANK YOU.
I BETTER BE GOING.

34:11.342 --> 34:13.428
[BELL RINGING]

34:17.181 --> 34:20.601
I, UH, MAY HAVE ACTED WITH
UNDUE HASTE, MR. INGALLS.

34:20.768 --> 34:23.855
I DO HOPE THIS PUTS
MATTERS RIGHT.

34:24.021 --> 34:25.022
IT DOES. THANK YOU.

34:25.189 --> 34:27.483
GOOD. NOW I MUST GET
BACK TO MY CHILDREN.

34:27.650 --> 34:28.776
SEE YOU AT HOME,
HALF-PINT.

34:28.943 --> 34:30.695
BYE, PA.

34:50.590 --> 34:55.178
[CHILDREN YELLING]

35:15.740 --> 35:18.826
[BELL RINGING]

35:24.999 --> 35:26.709
YUCK!

35:29.629 --> 35:31.088
[WHISPERING]
Get out! Get out!

35:31.255 --> 35:32.799
He's coming!

35:34.759 --> 35:37.762
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

35:45.269 --> 35:47.355
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]

35:59.367 --> 36:01.577
SILENCE!

36:07.583 --> 36:09.794
HERMAN, COME UP HERE!

36:09.961 --> 36:12.088
WHAT FOR?

36:13.339 --> 36:16.467
TO APOLOGIZE FOR
DESTROYING MY PROPERTY,

36:16.634 --> 36:18.886
TO CLEAN UP THE MESS
YOU'VE MADE,

36:19.053 --> 36:21.180
AND TO BE PUNISHED.

36:21.347 --> 36:23.933
NO. NOT ME.

36:24.100 --> 36:25.810
[OLDER BOYS
LAUGHING HYSTERICALLY]

36:25.977 --> 36:30.606
IN THIS CLASSROOM, WHEN THE BELL
RINGS, YOU WILL DO AS I SAY.

36:30.773 --> 36:33.192
HERMAN, COME HERE!

36:33.359 --> 36:35.319
NO, SIR.

36:36.487 --> 36:40.283
THEN I WILL COME TO YOU.

36:40.449 --> 36:43.160
HE DIDN'T DO IT.

36:45.580 --> 36:50.001
WELL, LAURA INGALLS.

36:50.167 --> 36:52.003
YOU SAY HERMAN
DIDN'T DO IT,

36:52.169 --> 36:55.840
THEN YOU MUST
KNOW WHO DID.

36:56.007 --> 36:58.551
YOU SAY HERMAN'S NOT GUILTY.
THEN, WHO IS?

36:58.718 --> 37:00.219
QUICKLY. TELL ME.

37:04.056 --> 37:08.603
YOU KNOW WHO DID IT,
AND YET YOU REFUSE TO TELL.

37:08.769 --> 37:10.521
THAT MEANS YOU'RE
PROTECTING SOMEONE,

37:10.688 --> 37:14.567
AND THAT SOMEONE
MUST BE YOURSELF.

37:14.734 --> 37:17.111
YOU DID IT!

37:17.278 --> 37:18.571
HOLD OUT YOUR HAND.

37:18.738 --> 37:20.156
[SLAM]

37:20.323 --> 37:22.992
DUMP ANOTHER BOOK,
AND YOU'RE ALL EXPELLED!

37:24.911 --> 37:29.540
AS FOR YOU, YOUNG LADY,
HOLD OUT YOUR HAND.

37:29.707 --> 37:31.876
Charles:
JUST A MINUTE.

37:35.212 --> 37:37.882
MR. INGALLS, WHAT, UH...

37:38.049 --> 37:41.177
WHAT BRINGS YOU HERE?

37:42.219 --> 37:45.014
MY DAUGHTER FORGOT
HER HOMEWORK.

37:45.181 --> 37:46.891
MARY, LAURA,
I WANT YOU TO GO HOME.

37:49.852 --> 37:53.230
YOU FIND ME IN
AN AWKWARD MOMENT.

37:53.397 --> 37:55.316
I'M HAVING A, UH...

37:55.483 --> 37:57.735
SMALL PROBLEM HERE.

37:57.902 --> 38:01.697
I HEARD YOUR SMALL PROBLEM
ALL THE WAY DOWN THE STREET.

38:06.535 --> 38:09.914
MR. INGALLS!
I'M TALKING TO YOU!

38:10.081 --> 38:11.666
I AM IN COMPLETE
CHARGE HERE.

38:11.832 --> 38:13.834
I WILL NOT TOLERATE
INTERFERENCE IN MY CLASSROOM.

38:14.001 --> 38:15.169
IF YOU WANT TO TALK
TO ME,

38:15.336 --> 38:16.754
I'LL BE AVAILABLE
AFTER SCHOOL HOURS.

38:16.921 --> 38:18.255
I'LL BE HERE AND SO
WILL THE SCHOOL BOARD.

38:18.422 --> 38:19.423
I'LL SEE TO THAT.

38:19.590 --> 38:21.092
HUMPH! EVERY PARENT
WITH A PROBLEM CHILD

38:21.258 --> 38:22.510
WANTS TO HIRE
A NEW TEACHER.

38:22.677 --> 38:24.345
MR. APPLEWOOD, I THINK
THE TEACHER'S THE PROBLEM.

38:24.512 --> 38:26.430
HOW DARE YOU
COME INTO--

38:28.391 --> 38:31.060
YOU OWE MY WIFE
A THANK YOU.

38:31.227 --> 38:33.396
SHE ASKED ME
TO BE NICE TO YOU.

38:55.167 --> 38:58.671
THERE IS ONLY ONE WAY TO KEEP
ORDER IN A CLASSROOM,

38:58.838 --> 39:00.548
AND THAT IS DISCIPLINE.

39:00.715 --> 39:04.301
AT TIMES, HARSH DISCIPLINE.

39:04.468 --> 39:07.179
SEE, I CAN MAKE THESE CHILDREN
TOE THE LINE,

39:07.346 --> 39:09.056
BUT ONLY IF I'M GIVEN
A FREE HAND.

39:09.223 --> 39:11.892
I CANNOT DO IT
IF PARENTS INTERFERE.

39:12.059 --> 39:13.561
[CHUCKLES]

39:13.728 --> 39:16.939
AND I SAY AGAIN THAT MR. INGALLS HAS
LAUNCHED THESE CHARGES AGAINST ME

39:17.106 --> 39:19.442
BECAUSE OF
HIS DAUGHTER'S FAILURE.

39:19.608 --> 39:23.487
NOW, I DEEPLY,
DEEPLY RESENT THAT.

39:23.654 --> 39:24.780
CHARLES?

39:27.199 --> 39:30.161
Charles: MR. APPLEWOOD, WHY
IS MY DAUGHTER FAILING?

39:30.327 --> 39:32.580
MR. INGALLS, I HARDLY THINK
THIS IS THE TIME OR PLACE

39:32.747 --> 39:34.165
TO GO INTO YOUR
DAUGHTER'S GRADES.

39:34.331 --> 39:35.750
WELL, THERE MUST BE
A REASON.

39:35.916 --> 39:41.964
YES, YES. SOME STUDENTS DO
NOT DO AS WELL AS OTHERS.

39:45.342 --> 39:49.346
I HAVE A FOLDER HERE THAT I
RECEIVED FROM MISS BEADLE.

39:49.513 --> 39:52.683
IT HAS SOME TEST PAPERS AND A
PROGRESS REPORT ON MY DAUGHTER.

39:52.850 --> 39:54.393
WOULD YOU LOOK AT IT,
PLEASE?

39:54.560 --> 39:55.811
I SEE NO REASON.

39:55.978 --> 39:57.021
I'M ONLY CONCERNED WITH
YOUR DAUGHTER'S WORK

39:57.188 --> 39:59.231
SINCE I HAVE BEEN
HER TEACHER.

39:59.398 --> 40:01.358
WELL, SO AM I.
VERY CONCERNED.

40:01.525 --> 40:03.110
BECAUSE I'M JUST
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT

40:03.277 --> 40:05.404
HOW MY LITTLE GIRL COULD GO FROM
ABOVE AVERAGE GRADES TO FAILURE.

40:05.571 --> 40:09.492
PERHAPS BECAUSE
SHE'S NOT TRYING.

40:10.534 --> 40:12.036
SHE'S NOT TRYING.

40:14.747 --> 40:17.917
LET ME READ SOME
OF THE REPORT TO YOU.

40:18.084 --> 40:19.877
"LAURA INGALLS IS
A HARDWORKING STUDENT.

40:20.044 --> 40:23.380
"HER WEAKEST SUBJECT IS
MATHEMATICS, MAINLY FRACTIONS.

40:23.547 --> 40:25.800
"HOWEVER, LAURA'S IMPROVED
GREATLY IN MATHEMATICS

40:25.966 --> 40:28.219
"DUE TO HER
EXCEPTIONAL EFFORT.

40:28.385 --> 40:31.555
SHE IS A FINE STUDENT AND A
PLEASURE TO HAVE IN MY CLASSROOM."

40:31.722 --> 40:33.891
MUST WE LISTEN
TO ALL THIS?

40:35.768 --> 40:38.646
YOU GOT THIS REPORT FROM
MISS BEADLE, AM I CORRECT?

40:38.813 --> 40:39.897
THAT'S CORRECT.

40:40.064 --> 40:42.566
OH. WELL,
THERE'S YOUR ANSWER.

40:42.733 --> 40:45.736
I'M SURE THAT
MISS BEADLE WOULD LIKE

40:45.903 --> 40:47.571
TO HAVE HER TEACHING
POSITION RESTORED TO HER,

40:47.738 --> 40:51.575
AND THEREFORE WOULD WRITE ANYTHING
ABOUT A STUDENT TO DISCREDIT ME.

40:51.742 --> 40:56.247
I'M AFRAID THAT I TEND TO AGREE
WITH MR. APPLEWOOD.

40:56.413 --> 41:00.417
SOMEONE TRYING TO GAIN BACK
EMPLOYMENT MIGHT WRITE ANYTHING.

41:00.584 --> 41:01.877
I AGREE WITH YOU,
MRS. OLESON.

41:02.044 --> 41:04.547
NELS, DO YOU HAVE THE RESUME MR.
APPLEWOOD SENT US?

41:04.713 --> 41:06.257
Nels: YES.

41:06.423 --> 41:08.050
OH. THANK YOU.

41:09.593 --> 41:12.847
THE, UH...THE RESUME.

41:13.013 --> 41:14.682
IT IS IN YOUR HANDWRITING,
ISN'T IT?

41:14.849 --> 41:16.725
OF COURSE.

41:16.892 --> 41:18.686
WELL, I WON'T GO THROUGH
ALL THE GLOWING REPORTS

41:18.853 --> 41:20.688
OF YOUR PAST TEACHING
ASSIGNMENTS.

41:20.855 --> 41:24.400
YOU TAUGHT AT A VERY, VERY IMPRESSIVE
NUMBER OF SCHOOLS. VERY IMPRESSIVE, INDEED.

41:24.567 --> 41:25.943
WELL, I HARDLY SEE
WHAT THAT, UH...

41:26.110 --> 41:29.947
WELL, IT'S VERY IMPRESSIVE.
IT'S JUST VERY LONG.

41:30.114 --> 41:31.782
WHY'D YOU LEAVE
YOUR LAST JOB?

41:31.949 --> 41:35.077
I WAS, UM...

41:35.244 --> 41:38.789
NOT SATISFIED WITH,
UH...

41:38.956 --> 41:41.458
ASPECTS OF THE JOB.

41:41.625 --> 41:43.961
AND THE JOB BEFORE THAT?

41:44.128 --> 41:45.212
PERSONAL REASONS.

41:45.379 --> 41:47.381
L-I'M NOT ON TRIAL
HERE, MR. INGALLS.

41:47.548 --> 41:49.216
OF COURSE NOT,
BUT YOU JUST SAID YOURSELF

41:49.383 --> 41:51.594
THAT A MAN WILL WRITE ALMOST ANYTHING
IN ORDER TO GAIN A POSITION.

41:51.760 --> 41:54.054
ARE YOU SAYING I MADE
FALSE STATEMENTS THERE?

41:54.221 --> 41:56.015
NO, I AM NOT. I'M SAYING
WE'RE A SMALL TOWN

41:56.182 --> 41:57.141
AND WE NEEDED A TEACHER

41:57.308 --> 41:58.934
AND WE TOOK YOUR RESUME
ON FACE VALUE.

41:59.101 --> 42:02.354
I THINK WE SHOULD SEND FOR YOUR
REFERENCES FROM YOUR FORMER EMPLOYERS.

42:02.521 --> 42:04.648
HOW DARE YOU!

42:06.692 --> 42:13.073
L--l CAME TO THIS TOWN BECAUSE
I THOUGHT I COULD HELP YOU,

42:13.240 --> 42:17.328
TO GIVE YOU THE--THE-- THE KIND OF
TEACHING AND DISCIPLINE YOU NEED,

42:17.494 --> 42:20.039
BUT...INSTEAD
OF APPRECIATION,

42:20.206 --> 42:22.499
I GET SUSPICION.

42:22.666 --> 42:24.835
YOU PROMISED ME
A FREE HAND

42:25.002 --> 42:27.004
TO TEACH THIS SCHOOL
AS I SAW FIT.

42:27.171 --> 42:29.965
NOW, IF THAT HAS CHANGED,
I WANT TO KNOW NOW.

42:30.132 --> 42:33.010
MR. APPLEWOOD,
CHARLES IS NOT SUGGESTING--

42:33.177 --> 42:34.887
I KNOW WHAT
HE'S SUGGESTING!

42:35.971 --> 42:37.765
TO GET REPORTS ON ME!

42:37.932 --> 42:41.185
OVER A CHILD
O-ONCE REPRIMANDED!

42:41.352 --> 42:43.520
NO, THAT IS NOT SO!

42:45.481 --> 42:47.316
I HAVE SEEN THE LIKES
OF YOU BEFORE.

42:47.483 --> 42:49.318
YOU WANT THE CHILDREN
TO TOE THE LINE,

42:49.485 --> 42:52.029
BUT YOU ARE AFRAID
TO DISCIPLINE THEM!

42:54.865 --> 42:59.078
THERE MUST BE ORDER!
THERE MUST BE ROUTINE!

42:59.245 --> 43:01.747
THERE MUST BE
RULES,

43:01.914 --> 43:05.542
AND THOSE RULES MUST
APPLY TO ALL STUDENTS!

43:05.709 --> 43:07.753
YOU CANNOT ALTER
THOSE RULES.

43:07.920 --> 43:08.712
YOU CANNOT...

43:08.879 --> 43:10.589
YOU CANNOT CHANGE
THAT ORDER.

43:10.756 --> 43:14.426
I MUST HAVE ORDER.

43:55.134 --> 43:59.179
MY RESIGNATION WILL BE ON
THE DESK IN THE MORNING.

44:05.936 --> 44:08.230
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

44:16.280 --> 44:17.990
MR. INGALLS, COME IN.

44:18.157 --> 44:20.576
I KNOW IT'S LATE, BUT I
SAW YOUR LIGHT WAS ON.

44:20.743 --> 44:22.953
WE HAD A MEETING AT SCHOOL
TODAY, AS YOU KNOW.

44:23.120 --> 44:23.954
YES.

44:24.121 --> 44:25.456
TO MAKE
A LONG STORY SHORT,

44:25.622 --> 44:27.374
MR. APPLEWOOD DIDN'T WORK OUT.
HE RESIGNED TODAY.

44:27.541 --> 44:29.001
OH.

44:29.168 --> 44:31.170
WE NEED A NEW TEACHER, AND WE'RE
HOPING YOU'LL TAKE THE JOB.

44:39.511 --> 44:40.554
SEE, THE BOARD THOUGHT
ALL IT WOULD TAKE

44:40.721 --> 44:41.722
IS SOMEBODY WITH
A STRONG HAND,

44:41.889 --> 44:45.476
AND THEY KNOW NOW
THEY WERE WRONG.

44:45.642 --> 44:47.478
THEY ALL WANT YOU BACK.

44:50.773 --> 44:54.443
AFTER EVERYTHING
THAT'S HAPPENED, I...

44:54.610 --> 44:56.362
I DON'T BLAME YOU
IF YOU SAY NO,

44:56.528 --> 44:58.322
BUT PLEASE
THINK ABOUT IT.

45:01.158 --> 45:04.912
I WANT TO COME BACK MORE
THAN ANYTHING IN THE WORLD.

45:05.079 --> 45:07.831
THOSE ARE MY CHILDREN,
AND I LOVE THEM, BUT...

45:07.998 --> 45:11.668
I DON'T THINK I CAN.

45:11.835 --> 45:13.879
MISS BEADLE, NO TEACHER
CAN DO IT ALONE.

45:14.046 --> 45:15.381
WE KNOW THAT NOW.

45:15.547 --> 45:17.508
THE PARENTS AND THE CHILDREN
ARE GOING TO HAVE TO HELP YOU.

45:20.677 --> 45:22.388
OH, IF I COULD ONLY
BE SURE OF THAT.

45:22.554 --> 45:24.598
TRY.

45:24.765 --> 45:26.517
YOU TOLD THAT TO
LAURA ENOUGH TIMES.

45:26.683 --> 45:28.477
ALL YOU CAN DO IS TRY.

45:32.815 --> 45:34.608
I'LL BE THERE
IN THE MORNING.

45:36.610 --> 45:38.320
THANK YOU.

45:58.465 --> 45:59.758
WHAT'D SHE SAY?

45:59.925 --> 46:01.301
SAID SHE'D BE IN SCHOOL
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.

46:01.468 --> 46:02.386
GOOD.

46:02.553 --> 46:03.595
I WANT YOU TWO TO
COME ON IN THE HOUSE.

46:03.762 --> 46:04.888
I WANT TO HAVE A LITTLE
TALK WITH YOU.

46:05.055 --> 46:06.390
DID WE DO
SOMETHING WRONG, PA?

46:06.557 --> 46:09.351
UH-UH. NO. WE'RE GOING TO DO
SOMETHING RIGHT.

46:09.518 --> 46:11.979
I MADE MISS BEADLE A PROMISE THAT
TOMORROW WHEN YOU GO TO SCHOOL,

46:12.146 --> 46:14.565
I WANT YOU TO HAVE A LITTLE TALK
WITH THE REST OF THE CHILDREN.

46:28.370 --> 46:29.746
[SLAM]

46:46.555 --> 46:48.390
[SLAM]

47:14.958 --> 47:17.002
SORRY, TEACHER.

47:17.169 --> 47:18.962
WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

47:19.129 --> 47:21.757
THANK YOU, HERMAN.

47:21.924 --> 47:23.300
I'M VERY HAPPY
TO HEAR THAT.

47:23.467 --> 47:26.762
YES, MA'AM.
